{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "brenton:psalms.105",
    "translationId": "brenton",
    "bookSlug": "psalms",
    "chapterNumber": 105,
    "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105",
    "summary": "Source text for Psalms 105 in Brenton's English Septuagint."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.105.1",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:1",
      "text": "Alleluia. - Give thanks to the Lord; for he is good: for his mercy endures for ever.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.105.2",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:2",
      "text": "Who shall tell the mighty acts of the Lord? who shall cause all his praises to be heard?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.105.3",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:3",
      "text": "Blessed are they that keep judgement, and do righteousness at all times.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.105.4",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:4",
      "text": "Remember us, O Lord, with the favour thou hast to thy people: visit us with thy salvation;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.105.5",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:5",
      "text": "that we may behold the good of thine elect, that we may rejoice in the gladness of thy nation, that we may glory with thine inheritance.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.105.6",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:6",
      "text": "We have sinned with our fathers, we have transgressed, we have done unrighteously.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.105.7",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:7",
      "text": "Our fathers in Egypt understood not thy wonders, and remembered not the multitude of thy mercy; but provoked him as they went up by the Red Sea.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.105.8",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:8",
      "text": "Yet he saved them for his name’s sake, that he might cause his mighty power to be known.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.105.9",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:9",
      "text": "And he rebuked the Red Sea, and it was dried up: so he led them through the deep as through the wilderness.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.105.10",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:10",
      "text": "And he saved them out of the hand of them that hated them, and redeemed them out of the hand of the enemy.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.105.11",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:11",
      "text": "The water covered those that oppressed them: there was not one of them left.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.105.12",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:12",
      "text": "Then they believed his words, and celebrated his praise.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.105.13",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:13",
      "text": "They made haste, they forgot his works; they waited not for his counsel.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.105.14",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:14",
      "text": "And they lusted exceedingly in the wilderness, and tempted God in the dry land.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.105.15",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:15",
      "text": "And he gave them their request, and sent fullness into their souls.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.105.16",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:16",
      "text": "They provoked Moses also in the camp, and Aaron the holy one of the Lord.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.105.17",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:17",
      "text": "The earth opened and swallowed up Dathan, and closed upon the congregation of Abiron.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.105.18",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:18",
      "text": "And a fire was kindled in their congregation, and a flame burnt up the sinners.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.105.19",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:19",
      "text": "And they made a calf in Choreb, and worshipped the graven image,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.105.20",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:20",
      "text": "and they changed their glory into the similitude of a calf that feeds on grass.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.105.21",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:21",
      "text": "They forgot God that saved them, who had wrought great deeds in Egypt;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.105.22",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:22",
      "text": "wondrous works in the land of Cham, and terrible things at the Red Sea.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.105.23",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:23",
      "text": "So he said that he would have destroyed them, had not Moses his chosen stood before him in the breach, to turn him away from the fierceness of his anger, so that he should not destroy them.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.105.24",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:24",
      "text": "Moreover they set at nought the desirable land, and believed not his word.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.105.25",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:25",
      "text": "And they murmured in their tents: they hearkened not to the voice of the Lord.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.105.26",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:26",
      "text": "So he lifted up his hand against them, to cast them down in the wilderness;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.105.27",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:27",
      "text": "and to cast down their seed among the nations, and to scatter them in the countries.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.105.28",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:28",
      "text": "They were joined also to Beelphegor, and ate the sacrifices of the dead. And they provoked him with their devices;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.105.29",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 29,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:29",
      "text": "and destruction, was multiplied among them.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.105.30",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 30,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:30",
      "text": "Then Phinees stood up, and made atonement: and the plague ceased.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.105.31",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 31,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:31",
      "text": "And it was counted to him for righteousness, to all generations for ever.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.105.32",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 32,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:32",
      "text": "They provoked him also at the water of Strife, and Moses was hurt for their sakes;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.105.33",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 33,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:33",
      "text": "for they provoked his spirit, and he spoke unadvisedly with his lips.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.105.34",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 34,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:34",
      "text": "They destroyed not the nations which the Lord told them to destroy;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.105.35",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 35,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:35",
      "text": "but were mingled with the heathen, and learned their works.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.105.36",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 36,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:36",
      "text": "And they served their graven images; and it became an offence to them.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.105.37",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 37,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:37",
      "text": "And they sacrificed their sons and their daughters to devils,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.105.38",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 38,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:38",
      "text": "and shed innocent blood, the blood of their sons and daughters, whom they sacrificed to the idols of Chanaan; and the land was defiled with blood.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.105.39",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 39,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:39",
      "text": "and was polluted with their works; and they went a whoring with their own devices.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.105.40",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 40,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:40",
      "text": "So the Lord was very angry with his people, and he abhorred his inheritance.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.105.41",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 41,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:41",
      "text": "And he delivered them into the hands of their enemies; and they that hated them ruled over them.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.105.42",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 42,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:42",
      "text": "Ands their enemies oppressed them, and they were brought down under their hands.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.105.43",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 43,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:43",
      "text": "Many a time he delivered them; but they provoked him by their counsel, and they were brought low by their iniquities.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.105.44",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 44,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:44",
      "text": "Ye the Lord looked upon their affliction, when he heard their petition.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.105.45",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 45,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:45",
      "text": "And he remembered his covenant, and repented according to the multitude of his mercy.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.105.46",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 46,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:46",
      "text": "And he caused them to be pitied in the sight of all who carried them captive.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.105.47",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 47,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:47",
      "text": "Save us, O Lord our God, and gather us from among the heathen, that we may give thanks to thy holy name, that we may glory in thy praise.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.105.48",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 48,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:48",
      "text": "Blessed be the Lord God of Israel from everlasting and to everlasting; and all the people shall say, Amen, Amen.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
